# Sun Sensor Prototype for Finland's First Satellite

For pictures & more information, see 

	http://BotBook.com/satellite

### Installing Development Environment

This is the quickest and the most effective way for advanced users. 
If this looks confusing, feel free to use vanilla Arduino IDE graphically. 

On xUbuntu 12.04
$ ./install-develtools.sh

Build and connect physical devices. See http://botbook.com/satellite

Connect master first, so it gets /dev/ttyACM0.  

$ make

### Make commands

- 'make' compiles master and slave to two Arduinos, then runs serial monitor. This 
  is the Sun Sensor Prototype.
- 'make e910' compiles and uploads a simple e910 "hello sunsensor" example
- 'make clean' removes object files etc
- 'make blink' wipes old code from Arduinos with Blink. 

